82","1313":"1313","1302":"1302","Abt 1265":"circa 1265","1255":"1255","1265":"1265","1282":"1282",", Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk",", Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1265–":"about 1265–Deceased","1255–1302":"1255–1302","1282–1313":"1282–1313","1265–Female":"1265–Deceased","Abt 1282":"about 1282","1313":"1313","1302":"1302","Abt 1265":"about 1265","1255":"1255","1265":"1265","1282":"1282",", Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom",", Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Venables","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: of Norman origin, a habitational name from Venables (Eure), perhaps named with Late Latin <i>venabulum</i> ‘hunting ground’ (a derivative of <i>venari</i> ‘to hunt’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Venable","meanings":["English: variant of   Venables  .","History: American bearers of this name are descended from Abraham Venables, who came to VA from England in or before 1687."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Venables was born about 1265, in Kinderton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Richard Donne III. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1265–":"umbes 1265–Surnud","1255–1302":"1255–1302","1282–1313":"1282–1313","1265–Female":"1265–Surnud","Abt 1282":"umbes 1282","1313":"1313","1302":"1302","Abt 1265":"umbes 1265","1255":"1255","1265":"1265","1282":"1282",", Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1265–":"noin 1265–Kuollut","1255–1302":"1255–1302","1282–1313":"1282–1313","1265–Female":"1265–Kuollut","Abt 1282":"noin 1282","1313":"1313","1302":"1302","Abt 1265":"noin 1265","1255":"1255","1265":"1265","1282":"1282",", Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1265–":"environ 1265–Décédée","1255–1302":"1255–1302","1282–1313":"1282–1313","1265–Female":"1265–Décédée","Abt 1282":"environ 1282","1313":"1313","1302":"1302","Abt 1265":"environ 1265","1255":"1255","1265":"1265","1282":"1282",", Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni",", Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Venables est née environ 1265, à Kinderton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Richard Donne III. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1265–":"um 1265–Verstorben",